We start by listing the prime factorization of 284: $$\begin{array}{r}2^2 \ \left \llcorner \\ \hline4\end{array}$$ $$\begin{array}{r}2\\ \hline2\end{array}\qquad$$ Now, we multiply the prime factor together to obtain all the divisors: $$\begin{array}{l}1,\ 2,\ 4,\ 71,\ 142,\ 284.\end{array}$$We remove 284, so our list of proper divisors of 284 is $$\begin{array}{l}1, 2, 4, 71, 142.\end{array}$$Therefore, the proper divisors of 284 are $\boxed{1,2,4,71,142}.$ The answer is: 1, 2, 4, 71, 142.
